Invention:  Vaccine
Year:       1796
Inventor:   Edward Jenner
Country:    England
Category:   Medicine
Description:Cowpox inoculation against smallpox
Impact:     Saved billions; smallpox eradicated; immunology foundation

Invention:  Penicillin
Year:       1928
Inventor:   Alexander Fleming
Country:    Scotland
Category:   Medicine
Description:First antibiotic from mold
Impact:     Saved estimated 200 million lives

Invention:  Telegraph
Year:       1837
Inventor:   Samuel Morse
Country:    USA
Category:   Communication
Description:Electrical coded message transmission
Impact:     First rapid long-distance communication

